Here are both approaches for navigating from a `ProductListPage` to `ProductDetailsPage`:

## 1. Register the Route

```csharp
// AppShell.xaml.cs
public AppShell()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
}
```

## 2. Navigate from ProductListPage

```csharp
// Approach A: Pass product ID as a query string
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?id={product.Id}");
}

// Approach B: Pass the full Product object
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
}
```

## 3. Receive Data on the ViewModel

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId { get => _productId; set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value); }
    public Product Product { get => _product; set => SetProperty(ref _product, value); }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A: string parameter from query string
        if (query.TryGetValue("id", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using the ID...
        }

        // Approach B: full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product product)
        {
            Product = product;
        }
    }
}
```

## 4. Wire the ViewModel to the Page

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- Query strings serialize to `string` — use for simple IDs/flags.
- `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` passes live objects — no serialization needed.
- `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel keeps your page code-behind clean.
- Always `await` `GoToAsync` to avoid race conditions.
